    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "## Problem\n\nChannel events (including UI events) and editor events are needlessly separated. For example, `VimLeave` already exists, but to \"listen\" for that even, a client has to set up a handler that then sends a custom event (or calls a client method). Or we have to create a new `exit` UI event that basically just duplicates `VimLeave`. https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/34365#issuecomment-2955820485\n\n## Expected behavior\n\n- Allow ~~nvim_ui_attach~~ any channel to opt-in to receiving editor events on the channel as msgpack-rpc notifications. The events will include the full serialized state of `v:event` and any `:help event-args`.\n    - *Requires* https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/35366\n- It's time to introduce `nvim_chan_set`, which sets channel properties. Or add `opts` param to `nvim_set_client_info` (requires [#31903](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/31903)).\n\n### Closed questions\n\n- No changes to `nvim_create_autocmd`, `nvim_clear_autocmds`, `nvim_exec_autocmds`. The channel is not a *scope* or an event source. \n- The channel does not define a *handler*. It is a passive subscriber that receives events as async notifications.",
